<!-- Node: "Q3MAP2 - Version 2.5.14 released" -->
<div class="body_box_header">Q3MAP2 - Version 2.5.14 released</div>
<div class="body_box"><small>Submitted by <a href="http://www.gamedesign.net/user/view/204" title="View user profile.">Miniwood</a> on Saturday, April 10, 2004 - 22:49</small><br /><br />
Ydnar announces the new version of <B>Q3MAP2</B>, the best compiler for Q3A and games based on the Q3A engine.  New features include:<br />
<br />
- New: -dirty mode courtesy of RaP7oR (dirtmapping/ambient occlusion)<br />
<br />
- New: q3map_skyLight code using more uniform angular distribution about the sky hemisphere<br />
<br />
- New: q3map_alphaMod set N.N<br />
<br />
- New: q3map_alphaMod scale N.N<br />
<br />
- New: q3map_alphaMod volume - applies all other q3map_alphaMod directives to each vertex inside a brush textured with this shader, allowing large faded scrolling fire shaders, waterfalls, marquees, explicit dotProduct terrain blending control, etc.
<br /><br />
<a href="http://assets.aq2world.com/archive/websites/www.gamedesign.net/node/view/220#comment" title="Jump to the first comment of this posting.">3 comments</a> &middot; <a href="http://assets.aq2world.com/archive/websites/www.gamedesign.net/node/view/220" title="Read the rest of this posting." class="read-more"><b>Read more</b></a> &middot; 121 reads
</div><br />


<!-- Node: "The Wadfather is back" -->
<div class="body_box_header">The Wadfather is back</div>
<div class="body_box"><small>Submitted by <a href="http://www.gamedesign.net/user/view/204" title="View user profile.">Miniwood</a> on Saturday, April 10, 2004 - 22:41</small><br /><br />
The site that calls itself <B>'The Ultimate Collection of Public Domain Graphics for Game Developers'</B> has relaunched with a new look and easier to use interface.<br />
<br />
<B>The Wadfather</B> is a great source for graphic files for Half-Life, Q3A and Unreal and currently boasts:<br />
<br />
    * 475 environment maps<br />
    * 184 texture collections with 17902 textures<br />
    * 62 desktop wallpapers<br />
<br />
The latest update is a new texture set by evillair based on the classic Quake 2 textures which you can download in Q3A, Half-Life & Unreal flavours.<br />
<br />
<A HREF="http://www.planethalflife.com/wadfather/">CLICK HERE</A> to pay your respects to The Wadfather
<br /><br />
<a href="http://www.gamedesign.net/comment/reply/219" title="Add a new comment to this page.">Add new comment</a>
</div><br />


<!-- Node: "Amit Doron's Interview" -->
<div class="body_box_header">Amit Doron's Interview</div>
<div class="body_box"><small>Submitted by <a href="http://www.gamedesign.net/user/view/1804" title="View user profile.">Kingpin_Xatrix</a> on Saturday, April 10, 2004 - 16:33</small><br /><br />
<!-- (c)2004 [DS]Kingpin_Xatrix -->

<b>Amit Doron</b>, Kingpin Lead Character Animator answered my questions<br> about <b>Kingpin</b> and violence in video games.<br><br>

<b>AMIT DORONS'S INTERVIEW</b><br><br>

<b>RUST:</b> Please tell us about yourself and how <br>you got into gaming business?<br><br>

<b>Amit Doron:</b> Being human - I'm creative, so about 13<br> years ago I started working at my father's studio, a <br>super-talented animator & director, on TV/ film<br>
animation spots, and in 94' I worked on my first title- <br>Cyclemania, bike racing game for Dos.. published by
<br /><br />
